# TemPy commit: include rebuilt binaries

When the user asks to commit and/or push TemPy (`python/tp`) changes:

- Always stage and commit rebuilt executables if they are modified: `python/tp/tp.exe` and `python/tp/tp.pyz`.
- Do not exclude them as "unrelated" or "binary rebuilds" when committing TemPy work.
- Prefer including them in the same commit as the source/docs/tests that produced them when possible; if they were left out of a prior commit, commit and push them promptly with the related TemPy change.
